</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/usomberlainwayfaerer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Somberlain Wayfaerer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(6/26/01 2:28:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wisdom of the collective minds.</span><hr size=1> Pporting for cash?  I don't know how I ever lived without it!  If I provide a service that uses my playing time, I have no moral or ethical doubts about porting for plat items.  That's not to say I won't do it for free, but I sure won't turn down some plat either.  And if someone asks for a port to Velious or an evac in Kunark, they should be willing to kick in a bit more.  <br>
<br>
I generally will SoW/buff people who ask nicely, if I'm not in the middle of something.  That does not include &quot;s0w me plz&quot;, because...<br>
<br>
1) It is not in the form of a question.<br>
<br>
2) &quot;plz&quot; is not a recognized word in my native English tongue.<br>
<br>
3) Even if it was a word, or was spelled properly, refer to #1...&quot;plz&quot; as part of an order is not a display of good manners or politeness.<br>
<br>
As for the pursuit of levels, I prefer to see Norrath at a more relaxed pace when possible.  I spent a month in lvl 51, and while I took longer than I cared for, I got to go to some neat places, attend my first dragon and planes raids, and get to know my guildmates and fellow Druzzil Ro residents better.  Play at a comfortable pace.<br>
<br>
<br>
